N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1241.33 - Traffic and parking

State Regulations

No vehicles, unless engaged in the transportation of
passengers or property, shall be allowed in any mooring facility; provided, however, that nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit access to
the mooring facilities by vehicles on emergency calls or by vehicles owned or
operated by the Port Authority. Notes
